Ltd. is a leader in digital transformation, specializing in intelligent automation, enterprise software solutions, and AI-driven innovation for automotive and manufacturing sectors. Our mission is to simplify complex workflows through smart, scalable solutions that enhance efficiency, reduce operational costs, and accelerate decision-making. 2. Project Requirements 2.1 Project Background Vehicle troubleshooting today relies heavily on manual reference to repair manuals, diagnostic PDFs, OEM knowledge bases, and historical service records. This process is slow, inconsistent, and highly dependent on technician expertise. We aim to build an Agentic Al-based troubleshooting assistant that can interpret manuals, understand symptoms, and guide technicians toward accurate step-by-step diagnosis. 2.2 Business Goal To automate and accelerate vehicle issue diagnosis by using AI agents that can read, interpret, and reason over technical manuals, fault codes, and historical data. 2.3 Problem to Solve Technicians currently: · Spend excessive time searching manuals · Depend on tribal knowledge · Lack consistent diagnostic guidance · Face challenges when manuals are fragmented across multiple documents The goal is to build an AI system that: · Reads and understands all manuals · Maps symptoms > probable root causes · Provides guided troubleshooting steps · Reduces service time and improves accuracy 2.4 Current State · Manuals exist across multiple PDF formats · No centralized search or indexing . No automated troubleshooting workflow · Troubleshooting steps vary between technicians 2.5 Project Scope Vendors must help design and build an agent-based AI troubleshooting solution: Required Capabilities · Document ingestion (PDF, images, manuals) · Text extraction and chunking · Embedding + vector search · Multi-agent system for: o Symptom understanding Troubleshooting step generation Root cause identification o Recommendation explanation · Ul for technicians · API layer for integrations · Observability & monitoring 2.6 Technology Expectations You may propose your preferred stack, but we currently use: · Azure Cloud (OpenAl, Blob, Functions) · Python for Al components . React for Ul · Vector DB (Azure Search, MongoDB Atlas, or local LLM options) 2.7 What We Expect to Be Built · End-to-end design · Al ingestion pipeline (PDF > text > embeddings > vector store) · Agentic workflow for troubleshooting · Suggestion ranking & confidence scoring · Ul design (technician dashboard + chat + recommendations) · Testing (unit, integration) · Deployment architecture (cloud or hybrid) 2.8 Management & Communication Requirements · Weekly sprint updates · Agile methodology · Collaboration via Teams/Jira · Documented APIs + architecture · NDA required 2.9 Roles Needed Vendors should include: · AI/ML Engineer · Agent Workflow Engineer · Backend Developer (Python/Node/.NET) · Ul Engineer (React) · QA Engineer · DevOps/Cloud Engineer 3. Project Budget and Timeline 3.1 Budget Proposals may include tiered pricing. We expect: · Cost breakdown by module · Licensing/hosting costs · Support & maintenance cost 3.2 Timeline Target duration: 10-16 weeks Key milestones should include: · Requirement analysis · Architecture & design · Prototype · Full implementation · Testing &

REQUEST FOR PROPOSAL (RFP) By [ABC Technologies Pvt. Ltd.] 1. Description of the Company ABC Technologies Pvt. Ltd. is an IT solutions provider delivering smart automation, AI- driven analytics, and enterprise-grade digital systems across multiple industries. We specialize in building intelligent platforms that optimize operations and enable data-driven decision making. 2. Project Requirements - Smart Inventory Management Using Sensors We are seeking proposals from qualified vendors to build an IoT-based Smart Inventory Management System that uses sensors, real-time tracking, and automated analytics to monitor inventory levels, predict stock usage, and reduce manual efforts. Business Goal To automate the current manual inventory tracking process using sensor-based monitoring and real-time alerts, enabling accuracy, efficiency, and predictive insights. Problem We Want to Solve Our current inventory workflow is: · Manual and time-consuming · Prone to errors · Lacks real-time visibility · Causes operational delays and stock inconsistencies Current System & Challenges · Inventory tracked on spreadsheets · Manual stock counts · No predictive analytics · No automated reorder alerts · Lack of historical movement insights Technology Stack (Preferred) · loT Sensors (RFID, weight sensors, ultrasonic sensors, BLE) · Azure IOT Hub / Event Hub · Azure Functions / API backend · Azure SQL / Cosmos DB · Power BI for reporting Expected Deliverables · Real-time sensor-based tracking system · Automated stock update engine · Alerts for low stock, anomalies, and expiry · Inventory usage analytics dashboard · Cloud deployment & documentation · Testing and monitoring setup Project Management Requirements · Weekly progress updates · Agile methodology · Git-based version control · Clear documentation of APIs, workflows, and deployments Team Requirements · loT Engineer · Backend/API Developer · Cloud Architect · QA Engineer · UI/UX Engineer (optional) Responsibilities Allocation Vendor will handle: · Design, development, sensor integration, and deployment · Dashboard creation · API and cloud services · Testing & stabilization ABC Technologies will provide: · Inventory workflows · Existing system access · Integration points · Acceptance criteria NDA Requirement A signed NDA is mandatory before project discussions and data sharing. 3. Project Budget & Timeline Vendors are expected to propose pricing based on effort. Expected timeline: 8-12 weeks. 4. Proposal Requirements Proposals must include: · Technical approach · Architecture diagram · Resource plan · Timeline & milestones · Cost estimation · Assumptions & exclusions Deadline for submission: 7 business days from RFP release. 5. Points of Contact Email: rfp@abctech.com Phone: +91-XXXXXXXXXX

Ltd. is a digital engineering and AI solutions provider focused on helping organizations modernize customer experience and operational processes. Business Goal To automate first-level customer interactions using Al, reduce support load by 40-60%, and provide faster, consistent responses to users. Problem We Want to Solve Current customer support team struggles with: · High volume of repeated queries · Delayed responses · No unified knowledge base · Manual triaging process Current System & Challenges · Email and call-based support · No automation or helpdesk integration · Lack of self-service support · Knowledge scattered across documents Technology Stack (Preferred) · Azure OpenAI (GPT-40 / GPT-40 mini) · Azure Search (optional) · Azure Bot Service / Web Chat · Integration with CRM / ticketing systems · Azure SQL / Cosmos DB Expected Deliverables · Conversational chatbot interface (web/mobile) · FAQ and document-based question answering · Intent classification and query routing · Multi-language support · Supervisor dashboard · Analytics and fallback mechanism · Deployment in Azure Project Management Requirements · Agile methodology · Weekly reviews · Complete documentation · Source code in Git Team Requirements · Conversational Al Engineer · Backend Developer · Cloud Engineer · QA Engineer · UX Designer Vendor Responsibilities · Understanding business workflows · Model fine-tuning or prompt engineering · API creation · Deployment · Testing & optimization NDA Requirement NDA signing required before sharing customer support logs or knowledge base data. 3. Project Budget & Timeline Estimated project duration: 6-10 weeks Budget to be proposed by vendor. 4. Proposal Requirements Each proposal must include: · Technical design · Bot capabilities · Training strategy · Deployment plan · Integrations required · Cost breakdown · Support & warranty details Deadline: 7 business days from the release of this RFP. 5. Points of Contact Email: rfp@abctech.com Phone: +91-XXXXXXXXXX

REQUEST FOR PROPOSAL (RFP) Project: E-commerce Website Development Issued by: Def Technologies Pvt. Ltd. 1. Company Overview Def Technologies Pvt. Ltd. is a digital solutions company specializing in web and mobile application development, cloud integration, and end-to-end enterprise solutions. We aim to provide modern, scalable, and user-friendly solutions to help businesses increase revenue, enhance customer experience, and streamline operations. We are now seeking a qualified vendor to design and develop a modern, responsive, and feature-rich e-commerce platform. 2. Project Requirements 2.1 Project Overview The objective is to build an end-to-end e-commerce platform that allows customers to browse products, place orders, make secure payments, and track deliveries. The platform should support both B2C and B2B transactions, be mobile-friendly, and offer an intuitive user experience. 2.2 Business Goals · Launch a scalable e-commerce website with responsive design. · Enhance customer experience with seamless navigation and checkout. . Enable secure payment processing and easy integration with multiple payment gateways. · Automate inventory management, order tracking, and reporting. · Support multi-language and multi-currency options (optional). · Integrate marketing and analytics tools for customer insights. 2.3 Scope of Work A. Frontend Development · Responsive web UI compatible with desktop and mobile. · Product catalog, search, filters, and sorting. · Shopping cart, checkout flow, and payment gateway integration. . Customer accounts, order history, and wishlists. . Admin dashboard for managing products, orders, and users. B. Backend Development · API layer for frontend and mobile integration. . User authentication, role management, and security. · Inventory management and order processing logic. · Reporting and analytics. C. Infrastructure & Deployment . Cloud hosting on Azure / AWS / GCP. · CI/CD pipeline setup. · Security best practices, including SSL, firewall, and secure storage. D. Testing & Quality · Functional testing and bug fixing. · Performance and load testing. · User acceptance testing (UAT). 2.4 Technology Stack (Preferred) · Frontend: React.js / Angular / Vue.js · Backend: Node.js / .NET Core / Python (Django/Flask) · Database: SQL (PostgreSQL / MySQL) or NoSQL (MongoDB) · Cloud / DevOps: Azure / AWS / GCP, Docker, CI/CD · Payment Integration: Stripe, Razorpay, PayPal, etc. · Optional: PWA support, SEO optimization, analytics tools 2.5 Project Management . Communication: Weekly calls via Teams/Zoom, daily Slack updates. · Methodology: Agile (Scrum/Kanban). . Tools: Jira / Azure DevOps for project tracking. · Documentation: Architecture diagrams, API docs, user manuals. 2.6 Roles Required · Project Manager / Scrum Master · Frontend Developer(s) · Backend Developer(s) · UI/UX Designer · QA Engineer · DevOps Engineer 2.7 Responsibilities Allocation Vendor Responsibilities: · Design, develop, test, and deploy the platform. · Provide project documentation and training. · Support post-deployment maintenance (optional). Def Technologies Responsibilities: · Provide brand guidelines, product catalogs, and business rules. · Approve wireframes, design, and milestones. . Provide access to any required third-party APIs or systems. 2.8 NDA Requirement Vendors must sign a Non-Disclosure Agreement before accessing any proprietary business data, product information, or documents. 3. Project Budget and Timeline · Budget: Vendors should provide detailed cost estimates

for design, development, deployment, and optional post-launch support. · Timeline: o Phase 1: Requirement analysis & wireframing - 2 weeks o Phase 2: UI/UX & frontend development - 4-6 weeks o Phase 3: Backend & integration - 4-6 weeks o Phase 4: Testing & UAT - 2-3 weeks o Phase 5: Deployment & handover - 1 week Total estimated project duration: 12-16 weeks. 4. Proposal Requirements Vendors must include in their proposal: 1. Company profile and relevant experience. 2. Proposed solution architecture and technical approach. 3. Project plan, milestones, and timeline. 4. Team composition with resumes. 5. Cost breakdown and payment schedule. 6. Risk assessment and mitigation strategy. 7. Any innovation or added value offered. Proposal Submission Deadline: DD/MM/YYYY 5. Point of Contact Name: [Project Manager / Contact Person] Email: [contact@deftech.com] Phone: [+91-XXXXXXXXXX] Address: Def Technologies Pvt. Ltd., Bangalore, India
